# =============================================================================
# dt-playbook-skills — .gitignore
# =============================================================================
# This repo publishes the source-of-truth playbook skills + thin agents under:
#   skills/dt-*/SKILL.md
#   agents/dt-*.md
#   ai.repo.yaml
#   README.md
#
# Everything below is either:
#   - runtime output produced by aimgr / dtctl / an agent locally, or
#   - upstream skills (dtctl operator skill, dynatrace-for-ai domain skills)
#     that this repo intentionally does NOT vendor — aimgr installs them
#     from the sources declared in ai.repo.yaml when a workspace applies
#     the manifest.
#
# If you need to install the upstream skills into this workspace for local
# testing, run the aimgr commands from README.md — the .gitignore entries
# below make sure those installed copies stay out of the git history.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# aimgr / agent-client runtime install targets
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# aimgr symlinks or copies installed skills + agents into your agent client's
# runtime directory. Keep the source (this repo) clean of them so upstream
# skills (dtctl, dt-obs-*, dt-app-*, dt-dql-essentials, dt-migration, …) can
# live locally without leaking into the repo.
.github/skills/
.github/agents/
.agents/
.claude/
.cursor/
.opencode/
.openclaw/
.kiro/
.junie/
ai.package.yaml

# Track the CI/PR templates if the repo eventually adds any — everything else
# in .github/ is agent-client runtime state.
!.github/workflows/
!.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/
!.github/pull_request_template.md
!.github/CODEOWNERS

# aimgr's local cache + registry state
.aimgr/
.aimgr-cache/

# npx / skills.sh scratch (if a teammate installs via npx instead of aimgr)
.skills-cache/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Playbook runtime output
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Written by the review playbooks when they run against a real tenant.
# Do NOT commit tenant data, mappings, or reports to this source repo.

# Per-workspace context ↔ folder mapping written by dt-playbook-common.
.dt-playbook-mappings.yaml

# Context folders created by the review playbooks. The naming convention is
# "<tenant>-<env>-<safety>/" (e.g. acme-prod-readonly/, demo-live-readonly/).
# Match the common safety suffixes so teammates can run playbooks against
# their own tenants without accidentally committing reports.
*-readonly/
*-readwrite-mine/
*-readwrite-all/
*-dangerously-unrestricted/
*-sprint/
*-prod/
*-dev/
*-staging/
*-playground/

# Sub-directories written by the playbooks (belt + braces — the parent
# context folder is already ignored above).
event-overview-reports/
logs-overview-reports/
process-detail-reports/
dashboards/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node / npx (needed for `npx skills add ...` if a teammate uses that path)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml
.pnpm-store/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Environment / secrets
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Never commit env files, tokens, or private keys — the playbooks never need
# them (dtctl handles auth via OS keyring), so these should always stay local.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
credentials.json
secrets.json

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor / IDE
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Track shared VS Code config if the team adds any; ignore per-user state.
.vscode/*
!.vscode/settings.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
!.vscode/tasks.json
!.vscode/launch.json
.history/

.idea/
*.iml
*.swp
*.swo
*.swn
*~

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS junk
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
desktop.ini
$RECYCLE.BIN/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Logs
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.log
logs/
